        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It seems that the return value annotation for `get_resolved_options`,  `vim.diagnostic.OptsResolved`, needs to be updated accordingly, since it currently only lists `table` for the `signs` value, because this is misleading; alternatively, `get_resolved_options` should be made to always return a table instead of `false`.\r\n\r\n0.12 is not affected by this because it does not have `get_resolved_options` and always uses `type()` for validation.",
